<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy — Sales Gorilla" %>

<h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-soft">Last updated: June 10, 2026</p>

<div class="legal mt-8">
  <p>
    Sales Gorilla (“Sales Gorilla”, “we”, “us”), operated by <strong>Tecaudex</strong>,
    provides a customer-relationship-management (CRM) platform at
    <strong>salesgorilla.app</strong>. This Privacy Policy explains what information we
    collect, how we use it, and the choices you have. By using Sales Gorilla you agree
    to this policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Who controls your data</h2>
  <p>
    Sales Gorilla is a business tool used by organizations (“Customers”) to manage their
    own sales leads and contacts. For the lead and contact records our Customers store in
    the platform, the Customer is the <strong>data controller</strong> and Sales Gorilla
    acts as a <strong>data processor</strong> on their behalf. For account and billing
    information of the Customer’s own users, Sales Gorilla is the controller.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account information</strong> — name, email, phone number and organization details of the users who sign in to Sales Gorilla.</li>
    <li><strong>Lead and contact data</strong> — information our Customers add or import about their prospects and customers, such as name, email, phone, company and notes.</li>
    <li><strong>Lead Ads data from Meta</strong> — when a Customer connects a Facebook Page, we receive the lead information a prospect submits through that Customer’s Facebook or Instagram Lead Ad forms (for example name, email, phone number and the answers to the form’s questions), together with the associated page, form, ad and campaign identifiers.</li>
    <li><strong>Integration data</strong> — content from third-party services a Customer connects, such as Google (Calendar, Gmail), Twilio (calls, WhatsApp) and Meta, used only to provide the requested features.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage and device data</strong> — log data, IP address and basic device/browser information collected automatically when you use the service.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To provide, operate and maintain the CRM and its integrations.</li>
    <li>To deliver leads from connected channels (including Meta Lead Ads) into the Customer’s account and notify the relevant team members.</li>
    <li>To authenticate users, secure the service and prevent abuse.</li>
    <li>To provide support and communicate service-related notices.</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell personal information.</p>

  <h2>Meta Platform data</h2>
  <p>
    Our use of information received from Meta (Facebook/Instagram) APIs follows Meta’s
    Platform Terms and Developer Policies. Lead data retrieved via the Meta Lead Ads
    integration is used solely to populate the connecting Customer’s CRM and is not used
    for any purpose unrelated to that Customer’s sales follow-up. A Customer can disconnect
    a Facebook Page at any time from <em>Settings → Features → Meta Lead Ads</em>, which
    stops further lead syncing.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We share information with service providers that host or power the platform (e.g. cloud
    hosting, and the integration providers a Customer enables), only as needed to deliver the
    service and under appropriate confidentiality obligations; with a Customer’s own authorized
    users; and where required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain lead and contact data for as long as the Customer maintains it in their account,
    and account data for as long as the account is active, unless a shorter period is required
    by law or requested as described below.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights &amp; data deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location you may have rights to access, correct, export or delete your
    personal information. End users whose data was captured through a Customer’s lead form
    should contact that organization (the controller). To request deletion of data held by
    Sales Gorilla, see our <%= link_to "Data Deletion instructions", data_deletion_path %>
    or email <a href="mailto:privacy@salesgorilla.app">privacy@salesgorilla.app</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use industry-standard measures including encryption in transit, encryption of sensitive
    credentials at rest, and access controls. No method of transmission or storage is 100%
    secure, but we work to protect your information.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by the
    “Last updated” date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:privacy@salesgorilla.app">privacy@salesgorilla.app</a>.
  </p>
</div>
